'''Kevin Lenini Gonçalves Pereira de Pina''' ({{IPA|pt|ˈkɛ.vin le.ˈni.ni ɡõ.ˈsal.vɨʃ pɨ.ˈɾej.ɾɐ dɨ ˈpi.nɐ|lang}}; born 27 January 1997) is a Cape Verdean professional footballer who plays as a [[defensive midfielder]] for Russian club [[FC Krasnodar|Krasnodar]] and the [[Cape Verde national football team|Cape Verde national team]].

==Club career==
A youth product of the Cape Verdean team Tchadense, Pina made his professional debut with [[U.D. Oliveirense|Oliveirense]] in a 3–2 [[LigaPro]] loss to [[S.L. Benfica B|Benfica B]] on 13 January 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2018/01/13/portugal/liga-de-honra/benfica-b/ud-oliveirense/2501602/|title=Benfica II vs. UD Oliveirense - 13 January 2018 - Soccerway|website=int.soccerway.com}}</ref> He shortly after went on loan to [[Anadia F.C.|Anadia]] and [[Sertanense F.C.|Sertanense]], before transferring to [[G.D. Chaves|Chaves]] in 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://inforpress.cv/futebol-internacional-cabo-verdiano-de-sub-20-kevin-pina-vai-representar-equipa-satelite-do-chaves-portugal/|title=Futebol: Internacional cabo-verdiano de sub-20 Kevin Pina vai representar equipa satélite do Chaves (Portugal) &#124; INFORPRESS|date=July 17, 2019|access-date=3 September 2021|archive-date=4 October 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231004222903/https://inforpress.cv/futebol-internacional-cabo-verdiano-de-sub-20-kevin-pina-vai-representar-equipa-satelite-do-chaves-portugal/|url-status=dead}}</ref>

On 8 September 2022, Pina signed a three-year contract with the [[Russian Premier League]] club [[FC Krasnodar|Krasnodar]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=FC Krasnodar|url=https://fckrasnodar.ru/team/news/object/?object_id=142419|title=ИГРОКОМ "КРАСНОДАРА" СТАЛ КЕВИН ЛЕНИНИ|trans-title=Kevin Lenini became a Krasnodar player|date=8 September 2022|access-date=8 September 2022|language=ru}}</ref> On 16 July 2024, he extended his contract to June 2027.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=FC Krasnodar|url=https://fckrasnodar.ru/team/news/object/?object_id=147505|title="КРАСНОДАР" ПРОДЛИЛ КОНТРАКТ С КЕВИНОМ ЛЕНИНИ|date=16 July 2024|language=ru}}</ref>

==International career==
Pina was called up to represent the [[Cape Verde national football team|Cape Verde national team]] for [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification]] matches in September 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://cazulgrena.com/kevin-pina-entre-os-eleitos-da-selecao-de-cabo-verde/|title=Kevin Pina entre os eleitos da seleção de Cabo Verde|date=August 25, 2021}}</ref> He debuted with Cape Verde in a 6–0 friendly win over [[Liechtenstein national football team|Liechtenstein]] on 25 March 2022.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.national-football-teams.com/matches/report/34151/Liechtenstein_Cape_Verde.html|title=Liechtenstein vs. Cape Verde|first=Benjamin|last=Strack-Zimmermann|website=www.national-football-teams.com}}</ref>

In December 2023, Pina was named in Cape Verde's squad for the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations]] in the [[Ivory Coast]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/cape-verde-name-veterans-mendes-vozinha-african-cup-nations-squad-2023-12-29/|title=Cape Verde name veterans Mendes, Vozinha in African Cup of Nations squad|date=30 December 2023|access-date=21 January 2023|website=Reuters}}</ref> He was in the starting line-up for Cape Verde's opening match against [[Ghana national football team|Ghana]], as the ''Tubarões Azuis'' defeated the four-time [[Africa Cup of Nations#Summary|African champions]] 2–1.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/67904849|title=Ghana 1-2 Cape Verde - Black Stars fall to late defeat|date=14 January 2024|access-date=21 January 2024|website=BBC Sport}}</ref> In the team's second match, he scored the final goal of a 3–0 win over [[Mozambique national football team|Mozambique]] which qualified Cape Verde for the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations knockout stage|knockout stage]] of the competition.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/67954111|title=Afcon 2023: Cape Verde 3-0 Mozambique|date=19 January 2024|access-date=21 January 2024|website=BBC Sport}}</ref>

